    ns1:bibliographyType "Bibliografía"@es .

<https://guia-kg.skai.etsisi.upm.es/resource/303000097/2025-26/evaluation> a ns1:EvaluationSystem ;
    ns1:evaluationDescription """Students opting for continuous evaluation will be asked to work in pairs and prepare a topic to present to their classmates. They must also submit the handwritten notes they plan to follow during the presentation. Their performance during the presentation will be worth three points, and the handwritten notes will be worth two points. At the end of the course, there will be an exam: the theory questions will be worth three points, and the problem-solving questions will be worth two points.

Students opting for a global evaluation will take a single exam at the end of the course. In this exam, the theory questions will be worth six points, and the problem-solving questions will be worth four points.

In July, there will be a resit exam. In this exam, the theory questions will be worth six points, and the problem-solving questions will be worth four points."""@es ;
